The paper deals with deep embedding methods in vision tasks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also introduces a new layer that is pluggable to any convolutional networks and is trained end-to-end, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also deals with image retrieval datasets, which suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper also discusses transfer learning and zero-shot learning on ImageNet datasets, which suggests that it may belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
